---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Missions — Custom40k Wiki">

<div class="missions-page">

  {/* ── Hero Header ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <div class="missions-hero">
    <div class="missions-hero-bg" aria-hidden="true" />
    <div class="missions-hero-content">
      <div class="missions-seal" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" width="72" height="72" fill="none">
          <polygon points="32,2 38,22 58,22 43,34 49,54 32,42 15,54 21,34 6,22 26,22" stroke="#a21217" stroke-width="1.5" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.08)"/>
          <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="12" stroke="#a21217" stroke-width="1" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)"/>
          <text x="32" y="36" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#a21217" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700">M</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <p class="missions-supertitle">Custom40k Supplement</p>
      <h1 class="missions-title">Missions</h1>
      <p class="missions-subtitle">7 missions across 3 engagement types · Tactical battlefield scenarios</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* ── Engagement Types ────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section reveal">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-line" />
      <h2 class="section-heading">Engagement Types</h2>
      <div class="section-line" />
    </div>
    <p class="section-intro">Each engagement type defines army size, AOP slots, and special restrictions. All engagements require at least 25% of points spent on Troops.</p>

    <div class="engagement-grid">

      {/* Skirmish */}
      <div class="engagement-card engagement-card--skirmish">
        <div class="engagement-header">
          <div class="engagement-badge">Skirmish</div>
          <div class="engagement-pts">1 000 – 1 500 pts</div>
        </div>
        <p class="engagement-flavour">A smaller clash between two factions.</p>

        <div class="aop-table-wrap">
          <div class="aop-label">Army Organisation</div>
          <table class="aop-table">
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>HQ</td><td>0–1</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Troops</td><td>1–3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Elites</td><td>0–1</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Fast Attack</td><td>0–1</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Heavy Support</td><td>0–1</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Dedicated Transport</td><td>0–1</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="restriction-block">
          <div class="restriction-heading">Unit Restrictions</div>
          <ul class="restriction-list">
            <li>HQ models may not take "once per army" upgrades.</li>
            <li>HQ units and Characters may not exceed 150 pts with upgrades.</li>
            <li>No single unit may exceed 300 pts with upgrades (Troops exempt).</li>
            <li>Squadron units may only field one model per slot.</li>
            <li>All units occupy an AOP slot, even if their rules state otherwise.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="restriction-block">
          <div class="restriction-heading">Stat &amp; Equipment Caps</div>
          <ul class="restriction-list">
            <li>No unit may have a 2+ armour save or better.</li>
            <li>No unit may have a 4+ invulnerable save or better.</li>
            <li>No unit may have Toughness 8 or better.</li>
            <li>No weapon may deal Damage 3 or better.</li>
            <li>No combined armour value of 34+ (Front+Side+Rear).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="restriction-block">
          <div class="restriction-heading">Special Rules</div>
          <ul class="restriction-list">
            <li>One unique Armory item per army.</li>
            <li>No allies. No Archetypes.</li>
            <li>No unit may cast more than one psychic power per turn.</li>
            <li>Recommended table: 48"×48" to 72"×48".</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Pitched Battle */}
      <div class="engagement-card engagement-card--pitched">
        <div class="engagement-header">
          <div class="engagement-badge">Pitched Battle</div>
          <div class="engagement-pts">2 500 – 3 500 pts</div>
        </div>
        <p class="engagement-flavour">A big battle between equal forces.</p>

        <div class="aop-table-wrap">
          <div class="aop-label">Army Organisation</div>
          <table class="aop-table">
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>HQ</td><td>1–2</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Troops</td><td>2–6</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Elites</td><td>0–3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Fast Attack</td><td>0–3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Heavy Support</td><td>0–3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Dedicated Transport</td><td>0–ᵀ *</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Fortification</td><td>0–1 *</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Flyer</td><td>0–2 *</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p class="aop-note">ᵀ One per Infantry selection. * Do not have to be filled to get another AOP.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="restriction-block">
          <div class="restriction-heading">Basics</div>
          <ul class="restriction-list">
            <li>25% minimum on Troops (including upgrades).</li>
            <li>Recommended table: 72"×48".</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Epic Battle */}
      <div class="engagement-card engagement-card--epic">
        <div class="engagement-header">
          <div class="engagement-badge">Epic Battle</div>
          <div class="engagement-pts">4 000+ pts</div>
        </div>
        <p class="engagement-flavour">All-out war.</p>

        <div class="aop-table-wrap">
          <div class="aop-label">Army Organisation</div>
          <table class="aop-table">
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>HQ</td><td>1–2</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Troops</td><td>2–6</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Elites</td><td>0–3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Fast Attack</td><td>0–3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Heavy Support</td><td>0–3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Dedicated Transport</td><td>0–ᵀ *</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Fortification</td><td>0–1 *</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Flyer</td><td>0–2 *</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td>Lords of War</td><td>0+ *</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p class="aop-note">ᵀ One per Infantry selection. * Do not have to be filled to get another AOP.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="restriction-block">
          <div class="restriction-heading">Basics</div>
          <ul class="restriction-list">
            <li>25% minimum on Troops (including upgrades).</li>
            <li>Lords of War capped at 33% of total points.</li>
            <li>Minimum recommended table: 72"×48".</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ── Scoring ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section reveal">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-line" />
      <h2 class="section-heading">Scoring</h2>
      <div class="section-line" />
    </div>
    <div class="scoring-grid">
      <div class="scoring-card">
        <div class="scoring-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" width="32" height="32" fill="none">
            <path d="M16 4 L20 14 L30 14 L22 20 L25 30 L16 24 L7 30 L10 20 L2 14 L12 14 Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="scoring-title">Attrition</div>
        <p class="scoring-desc">Units are worth their point cost in VP when destroyed by end of round 5. Units at or below half strength are worth 50% of their cost. Single-model units use remaining Wounds/HP to determine value.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scoring-card">
        <div class="scoring-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" width="32" height="32" fill="none">
            <circle cx="16" cy="16" r="12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
            <circle cx="16" cy="16" r="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
            <line x1="16" y1="4" x2="16" y2="11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <line x1="16" y1="21" x2="16" y2="28" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <line x1="4" y1="16" x2="11" y2="16" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <line x1="21" y1="16" x2="28" y2="16" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="scoring-title">Mission Objectives</div>
        <p class="scoring-desc">Hold an objective by keeping at least one model within 3" of it with no enemy model in range. If both sides have models in range, the objective is contested. Elevation: units one level above or below can contest.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scoring-card">
        <div class="scoring-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" width="32" height="32" fill="none">
            <rect x="6" y="6" width="20" height="20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
            <path d="M6 20 L16 10 L26 20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="scoring-title">Winning</div>
        <p class="scoring-desc">After round 5, count all VP for each side. A player wins by having at least <strong>100 more VP</strong> than the opponent. Otherwise the game is a draw.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ── Secondary Objectives ────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section reveal">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-line" />
      <h2 class="section-heading">Secondary Objectives</h2>
      <div class="section-line" />
    </div>
    <p class="section-intro">Used by all missions unless stated otherwise. Each secondary objective is worth <strong>200 VP</strong>.</p>
    <div class="secondaries-grid">
      <div class="secondary-card">
        <div class="secondary-name">Hold the Line</div>
        <p class="secondary-desc">By end of round 5, no enemy unit may be within your own deployment zone.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="secondary-card">
        <div class="secondary-name">Linebreaker</div>
        <p class="secondary-desc">By end of round 5, at least one friendly unit must be within the enemy's deployment zone.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="secondary-card">
        <div class="secondary-name">Relic Hunt</div>
        <p class="secondary-desc">For objective-marker missions only. When an objective outside any deployment zone is controlled for the first time, roll a die — on 5+ it becomes a relic worth +100 extra VP at game end.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="secondary-card">
        <div class="secondary-name">Save the Warlord</div>
        <p class="secondary-desc">Your highest-cost HQ unit must survive to end of round 5. If tied, choose before deployment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="secondary-card">
        <div class="secondary-name">Slay the Warlord</div>
        <p class="secondary-desc">The enemy's highest-cost HQ unit must be destroyed by end of round 5. If tied, opponent chooses before deployment.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ── Missions ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section reveal">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-line" />
      <h2 class="section-heading">Mission List</h2>
      <div class="section-line" />
    </div>

    {/* ── Skirmish ── */}
    <div class="engagement-label engagement-label--skirmish">
      <span>Skirmish Missions</span>
    </div>

    {/* Mission 1: Control */}
    <div class="mission-card reveal">
      <div class="mission-header">
        <span class="mission-num">01</span>
        <h3 class="mission-name">Control</h3>
        <span class="mission-type-badge mission-type--skirmish">Skirmish</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mission-body">
        <div class="mission-map">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 200 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="map-svg">
            {/* Board */}
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="122" fill="#e8dfc8" rx="2"/>
            {/* Deploy zones (diagonal quarters) */}
            <polygon points="4,4 100,4 100,69 4,69" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)"/>
            <polygon points="100,65 196,65 196,126 100,126" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)"/>
            {/* Deploy labels */}
            <text x="40" y="38" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#a21217" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700" opacity="0.7">P1</text>
            <text x="160" y="105" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#a21217" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700" opacity="0.7">P2</text>
            {/* Dividing lines */}
            <line x1="100" y1="4" x2="100" y2="126" stroke="#394950" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3" opacity="0.4"/>
            <line x1="4" y1="65" x2="196" y2="65" stroke="#394950" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3" opacity="0.4"/>
            {/* Objectives */}
            <circle cx="52" cy="35" r="7" fill="#a21217"/>
            <text x="52" y="38" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
            <circle cx="148" cy="35" r="7" fill="#394950"/>
            <text x="148" y="38" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
            <circle cx="52" cy="96" r="7" fill="#394950"/>
            <text x="52" y="99" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
            <circle cx="148" cy="96" r="7" fill="#a21217"/>
            <text x="148" y="99" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
            {/* Border */}
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="122" fill="none" stroke="#9a8060" stroke-width="1.5" rx="2"/>
          </svg>
          <div class="map-legend">
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot legend-dot--red"></span>Objective</span>
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-box legend-box--red"></span>Deployment</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mission-rules">
          <div class="mission-setup">
            <div class="rules-label">Set-Up</div>
            <ol class="setup-steps">
              <li>Divide the board into four quarters and place an objective marker in the middle of each.</li>
              <li>Both players roll a die; the highest score picks which quarter to deploy in. The other player's deployment zone is the opposite quarter.</li>
              <li>Starting with the winner of the roll, both players alternate deploying one unit at a time.</li>
              <li>No unit can be deployed within 9" of the centre of the table at game start.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
          <div class="victory-box">
            <div class="victory-label">Victory Condition</div>
            <div class="victory-title">Control Table Quarters</div>
            <p>To control a table quarter, a unit must control the mission objectives inside it. A unit can only occupy one quarter — if spread over more than one, roll randomly. At the end of each battle round, a player scores <strong>200 VP</strong> per controlled table quarter.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Mission 2: Salvage */}
    <div class="mission-card reveal">
      <div class="mission-header">
        <span class="mission-num">02</span>
        <h3 class="mission-name">Salvage</h3>
        <span class="mission-type-badge mission-type--skirmish">Skirmish</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mission-body">
        <div class="mission-map">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 200 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="map-svg">
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="122" fill="#e8dfc8" rx="2"/>
            {/* Deploy zones top + bottom strips */}
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="22" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)" rx="2"/>
            <rect x="4" y="104" width="192" height="22" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)" rx="2"/>
            <text x="100" y="17" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#a21217" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700" opacity="0.7">P1 DEPLOY</text>
            <text x="100" y="117" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#a21217" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700" opacity="0.7">P2 DEPLOY</text>
            {/* 9 objectives in 3×3 grid */}
            {([33,100,167] as const).flatMap(cx =>
              ([40,65,90] as const).map(cy => (
                <g>
                  <circle cx={cx} cy={cy} r="6" fill="#6b5030"/>
                  <text x={cx} y={cy+3} text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#e8dfc8" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
                </g>
              ))
            )}
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="122" fill="none" stroke="#9a8060" stroke-width="1.5" rx="2"/>
          </svg>
          <div class="map-legend">
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot legend-dot--brown"></span>Wreckage (×9)</span>
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-box legend-box--red"></span>Deployment</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mission-rules">
          <div class="mission-setup">
            <div class="rules-label">Set-Up</div>
            <ol class="setup-steps">
              <li>Place 9 mission objectives (wreckage) evenly distributed on the field.</li>
              <li>Both players roll a die; the winner chooses which table edge to deploy along. Their opponent gets the opposite edge.</li>
              <li>Starting with the winner of the roll, both players alternate deploying one unit at a time.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
          <div class="victory-box">
            <div class="victory-label">Victory Condition</div>
            <div class="victory-title">Collect Wreckage / Attrition</div>
            <p>To collect wreckage, a unit must be in base contact with the objective and use a <em>Stand &amp; Shoot</em> command to pick it up. A unit can only hold one wreckage. Securing wreckage scores <strong>200 VP</strong> per piece; the objective is then removed. Additionally, VP are awarded for destroyed enemy units.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* ── Pitched Battle ── */}
    <div class="engagement-label engagement-label--pitched">
      <span>Pitched Battle Missions</span>
    </div>

    {/* Mission 3: Frontlines */}
    <div class="mission-card reveal">
      <div class="mission-header">
        <span class="mission-num">03</span>
        <h3 class="mission-name">Frontlines</h3>
        <span class="mission-type-badge mission-type--pitched">Pitched Battle</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mission-body">
        <div class="mission-map">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 200 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="map-svg">
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="122" fill="#e8dfc8" rx="2"/>
            {/* Deploy zones left + right strips */}
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="36" height="122" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)" rx="2"/>
            <rect x="160" y="4" width="36" height="122" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)" rx="2"/>
            <text x="22" y="10" text-anchor="middle" font-size="6.5" fill="#a21217" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700" opacity="0.8" writing-mode="vertical-lr" transform="translate(22,70) rotate(-90)">P1</text>
            <text x="178" y="10" text-anchor="middle" font-size="6.5" fill="#a21217" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700" opacity="0.8" writing-mode="vertical-lr" transform="translate(178,70) rotate(90)">P2</text>
            {/* Command posts */}
            <rect x="28" y="22" width="14" height="14" fill="none" stroke="#394950" stroke-width="2"/>
            <text x="35" y="32" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#394950" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700">CP</text>
            <rect x="158" y="94" width="14" height="14" fill="none" stroke="#394950" stroke-width="2"/>
            <text x="165" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#394950" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="700">CP</text>
            {/* 3 objectives in center column */}
            <circle cx="100" cy="30" r="7" fill="#a21217"/>
            <text x="100" y="33" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
            <circle cx="100" cy="65" r="7" fill="#a21217"/>
            <text x="100" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
            <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="7" fill="#a21217"/>
            <text x="100" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
            {/* 18" scanner zone (dashed ring around CP) */}
            <circle cx="35" cy="29" r="22" fill="none" stroke="#394950" stroke-width="0.8" stroke-dasharray="3,2" opacity="0.4"/>
            <circle cx="165" cy="101" r="22" fill="none" stroke="#394950" stroke-width="0.8" stroke-dasharray="3,2" opacity="0.4"/>
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="122" fill="none" stroke="#9a8060" stroke-width="1.5" rx="2"/>
          </svg>
          <div class="map-legend">
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot legend-dot--red"></span>Objective</span>
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-sq legend-sq--steel"></span>Command Post</span>
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-circle-dash"></span>18" scanner</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mission-rules">
          <div class="mission-setup">
            <div class="rules-label">Set-Up</div>
            <ol class="setup-steps">
              <li>Place one command post in each deployment zone (Position: 12" in, 12" up from corner).</li>
              <li>Place three objectives in a line between both deployment zones.</li>
              <li>Each command post has an 18" scanner/jammer: no unit may deploy within 18" of the enemy command post. Deep Strike scatters into this zone return to reserves.</li>
              <li>Both players roll a die; the winner chooses deployment side. Alternate deploying one unit at a time.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
          <div class="victory-box">
            <div class="victory-label">Victory Condition</div>
            <div class="victory-title">Control Objectives / Sabotage Command Post</div>
            <p>Controlling one objective at end of a battle round scores <strong>200 VP</strong>. If a player occupies the enemy's command post, they win automatically regardless of VP. If both lose their command posts in the same round, the higher VP player wins.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Mission 4: Take & Hold */}
    <div class="mission-card reveal">
      <div class="mission-header">
        <span class="mission-num">04</span>
        <h3 class="mission-name">Take &amp; Hold</h3>
        <span class="mission-type-badge mission-type--pitched">Pitched Battle</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mission-body">
        <div class="mission-map">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 200 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="map-svg">
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="122" fill="#e8dfc8" rx="2"/>
            {/* Deploy zones */}
            <rect x="4" y="4" width="36" height="122" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)" rx="2"/>
            <rect x="160" y="4" width="36" height="122" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.12)" rx="2"/>
            {/* Quarter lines */}
            <line x1="4" y1="65" x2="196" y2="65" stroke="#394950" stroke-width="0.8" stroke-dasharray="4,3" opacity="0.3"/>
            {/* Center objective */}
            <circle cx="100" cy="65" r="8" fill="#a21217"/>
            <text x="100" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
            {/* Diagonal pair — 12" in, 12" up from corners */}
            <circle cx="60" cy="28" r="7" fill="#a21217"/>
            <text x="60" y="31" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="white" font-family="sans-serif">★</text>
